        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 12:24PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 1224 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Town Creek, or 13 miles northwest of Moulton. This thunderstorm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Town Creek, Leighton, Ne Smith, Whiteoak, and La Grange.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
